actions:
git remote - view and create remotes
git remote add name_of_remote //(only 1, standard name origin) url_of_remote
git push name_of_remote branch_name (master)
vocab:
remote - remote repository, store location of repository you will want to send/receive to/from

When you push a branch, all commits associated with it (except for ones already on github) will be sent.

1. When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work local?
I would want to use a remote repository when working on a collaborative project or when working on a project for someone in order to be able to present my work to more than one person.
